%p
  Connecting people to wildlife in a positive way -
  through knowledge and understanding - the Hope for Wildlife Society
  believes that education through rehabilitation is the key
  to a sustainable future. 
  
%p
  Our mission comprises three important goals:
  %ol
    %li
      Rehabilitation and release into the wild of injured and
      orphaned wildlife.
    %li
      Education of our children and the general public regarding
      the importance of conservation of various wildlife species
      and the ecosystems that sustain them.
    %li
      Research to develop the knowledge and understanding necessary
      for conservation and management of wildlife resources in a complex
      and continually changing biological, social and political environment.
